<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><U><META NAME="CHANGEDBY" CONTENT="Mridul Chopra"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4 STYLE="font-size: 16pt"><B>INTRODUCTION</B></U></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=CENTER STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><BR><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4><U><B>TITLE
OF PROJECT</B></U></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4><U>:</U></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>BookShelf</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4><U><B>INTRODUCTION</B></U></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>BookShelf
is a online orders and stock Register. A Stock Register is a software
program that helps the user(s) or businessmen or accountants to keep
record of various items that are currently present in stock.
Moreover, a stock register also facilitates a user by allowing
him/her keeping a record of various purchases made and sales
generated on daily basis. Thus, sales and purchase modules work
independently but must work in synchronization to provide consistent
data.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Most
of the today&rsquo;s businessmen especially small and middle class
still depend upon the traditional paper based methods to keep track
of their sales, purchase and manage their stocks accordingly.
Although this traditional method is still considered reliable but it
has many shortcomings too. Traditional paper based technology is a
time consuming method and requires a lot of labour. Moreover, it is
vulnerable to human errors which in case of business might prove to
be fatal. Inconsistency in data is also quite frequently observed.
Backup procedures are also less implemented in traditional systems
majorly because of increase in labour cost and time required to
implement this. </FONT></FONT></FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>The
proposed system eliminates all the above problems hence it has become
highly popular among various professionals and is also recommended by
various businessmen for smooth management of their stocks.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><BR><BR>
</P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4><U><B>OBJECTIVES</B></U></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>The
primary objective of a Stock Register is &ldquo;ease of maintenance
of stocks /records&rdquo;. An acceptable stock register must also
fulfil other objectives which are described below:</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>1.
</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Facilitate
ease of maintenance of stocks.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>2.</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Reduce
cost of maintenance of records.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>3.</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Reduce
overall time involved in record maintenance.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>4.</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Ensure
Data Consistency and Integrity.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>5.</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Conduct
Authorisation of accessing party. </FONT></FONT></FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>6.
</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Provide
interactive view or user friendly view to the user.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>7.
</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Have
an abstract mechanism which automatically updates stocks on
sales/purchase entries.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>8.</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Provide
mechanism by which user can delete the unwanted entries.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>9.
</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Provide
mechanism by which user can alter the records entered without data
being getting inconsistent.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><B>10.</B></FONT></FONT></FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a">
</FONT><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>Provide
Mechanism by which user can view the records (sales or purchase).</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4><U><B>Pros
and Cons</B></U></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=4><U>Pros:</U></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>1.
Maintenance of stocks becomes easier.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>2.
This System also reduces cost of maintenance.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>3.
This System also involves less use of labor.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>4.
Integrity of data is ensured by use of appropriate DBMS.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>5.
Backup procedures of stocks becomes very easy and less time consuming
as compared to traditional paper based stock management system.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>6.
Only trusted users are allowed to access the data. Therefore, data
security is ensured by stock register.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>7.
One of the advantages of using inbuilt Stock Register is that user
does not need to have any knowledge or experience of stock handling.
He or She only needs to enter the data and record maintenance will be
done automatically by the application.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>8.
If records get damaged appropriate recovery procedure can be applied
to ensure that data is gained back.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=JUSTIFY STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>9.
Stock Register gives real time access to data.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>10.
Stock Register also provides user with other useful features which
makes stock maintenance easier and facilitates business functions. </FONT></FONT></FONT>
</P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3><U>Cons:</U></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>1.
Stock Register application requires knowledge of computer
applications.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>2.
To recover the data technical support is required.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>3.
Crash of computer system may lead to loss of entire data.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>4.
It might become difficult initially for a user to understand the
system.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>5.
Careful inspection of the system is required before fully
functionally implementing it.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>6.
Frequent Maintenance of the proposed system is required.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>7.
Stock Register application is quite expensive as compared to
traditional systems.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN=LEFT STYLE="margin-bottom: 0.14in; line-height: 0.17in"><FONT COLOR="#00000a"><FONT FACE="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT SIZE=3>8.
Most of the business organisations have different requirements than
the others, therefore, Stock Register need to be customised
independently for each of them which makes it tedious and time
consuming task for the developers.</FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
